Low offer in S . Lanka diesel , jet tender from Shell . The lowest offer in Sri Lanka ' s tender to buy gas oil and jet fuel for July 12 - 13 delivery was made by Shell , an official with state - owned Ceylon Petroleum Corp ( CPC ) said on Wednesday . The offer for 250 , 000 barrels of 1 . 0 - percent sulphur gas oil was at a discount of 13 . 5 cents per barrel to Singapore spot quotes and for 50 , 000 barrels of jet fuel at 18 . 5 cents per barrel discount to Singapore spot quotes , cost - and - freight ( c - and - f ) Colombo . The tender , which attracted six offers , closed on June 18 and would be awarded later this evening . The official said CPC would decide on June 24 to issue another tender to buy gas oil and jet fuel which could be for July 30 - 31 delivery . In its previous tender for June 27 - 28 delivery , CPC bought from Dutch trader Vitol 250 , 000 barrels of gas oil at an 11 . 5 - cent discount to Singapore spot quotes , and 50 , 000 barrels of jet fuel at a 6 . 5 - cent discount , c - and - f Colombo . - - Singapore Newsroom ( + 65 - 870 3084 ) 
